{"id":574258,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bertram_Kostant","text":"Bertram Kostant (May 24, 1928 \u2013 February 2, 2017) was an American mathematician. He was known for his works in Kostant partition function and Kostant\u2013Parthasarathy\u2013Ranga Rao\u2013Varadarajan determinants. In 2016, he won the Wigner Medal. He worked at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology and at the University of California, Berkeley.\nKostant was born in Brooklyn, New York. He studied at the University of Chicago.\nKostant died at a rehabilitation center in Roslindale, Massachusetts on February 2, 2017 from stroke complications, aged 88.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Americans","surface_form":"American","offset":57},{"uri":"Mathematician","surface_form":"mathematician","offset":66},{"uri":"Kostant_partition_function","surface_form":"Kostant partition function","offset":111},{"uri":"Kostant%E2%80%93Parthasarathy%E2%80%93Ranga_Rao%E2%80%93Varadarajan_determinants","surface_form":"Kostant\u2013Parthasarathy\u2013Ranga Rao\u2013Varadarajan determinants","offset":142},{"uri":"Wigner_Medal","surface_form":"Wigner Medal","offset":220},{"uri":"Massachusetts_Institute_of_Technology","surface_form":"Massachusetts Institute of Technology","offset":251},{"uri":"University_of_California%2C_Berkeley","surface_form":"University of California, Berkeley","offset":300},{"uri":"Brooklyn","surface_form":"Brooklyn","offset":356},{"uri":"New_York_(state)","surface_form":"New York","offset":366},{"uri":"University_of_Chicago","surface_form":"University of Chicago","offset":394},{"uri":"Rehabilitation_center","surface_form":"rehabilitation center","offset":435},{"uri":"Roslindale%2C_Massachusetts","surface_form":"Roslindale","offset":460},{"uri":"Massachusetts","surface_form":"Massachusetts","offset":472},{"uri":"Stroke","surface_form":"stroke","offset":511}]}